 4 12:54:56 2026 +0530\n\n    Add Atlas Harness Eval trace (per-run benchmark instrument)\n    \n    buildHarnessTrace flattens a recorded ProofRun into a flat JSON trace for\n    benchmarking the architecture, not just the outcome: tool-call counts by name\n    (parsed from event kinds), edited files, checks, diagnostics, failures, repo-map\n    usage, duration, drop counts. Pure and derived only from recorded data - token\n    counts are deliberately omitted (live-run only, not in the journal) rather than\n    faked. +3 tests.\n    \n    This is GPT review P0: the instrument that answers 'did repo map / LSP / memory\n    actually help' once benchmark runs are recorded.\n    \n    Verified (clean shell): tsc 0, harnessTrace tests 3/3.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\ncommit a054c67e507e804af7699d35987149ec4fe18062\nAuthor: MDSD0 <crypticmite@gmail.com>\nDate:   Thu Jun 4 12:51:13 2026 +0530\n\n    Honest 5-tier proof verdict (no more echo-ok = passed)\n    \n    GPT review flagged the proof verdict as too weak: any exit-0 foreground shell\n    marked a run 'passed', so a bare 'echo ok' looked verified - dishonest for a\n    proof-oriented harness. Replace the binary passed/incomplete with soft,\n    non-blocking tiers that never overclaim:\n    \n      verified      - a recognized test/build/typecheck/lint command exited 0\n      smoke_checked - some command ran ok, but no recognized check\n      completed     - edits happened, no command run\n      unverified    - nothing meaningful to check\n      failed / cancelled - unchanged\n    \n    isRecognizedCheck() matches test/vitest/pytest/tsc/lint/cargo/go/build/etc.\n    The run is never blocked; only the verdict label gets honest. ReceiptStrip,\n    reliabilitySummary (verified vs softPass), and the affected fixtures updated.\n    +3 tests: echo->smoke_checked, cargo test->verified, read-only->unverified.\n    \n    Verified (clean shell, verify-atlas.sh --all exit 0): tsc 0, vi